# Implementation Plan - SentinelAgent Python Backend

Build a highly concurrent Python backend for SentinelAgent with FastAPI, Amazon Bedrock (`boto3` + Claude 3.5 Sonnet), and CockroachDB (`psycopg2` vector cosine similarity search).

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> - **Amazon Bedrock Credentials**: The backend requires valid AWS credentials (`AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID`, `AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY`, `AWS_REGION`) with permissions for Bedrock Claude 3.5 Sonnet (`anthropic.claude-3-5-sonnet-20241022-v2:0`). A mock/fallback streaming mode will be included for local development if AWS credentials are not configured.
> - **CockroachDB Connection**: The database connection string must be provided via `DATABASE_URL` in `.env`. A fallback SQLite/in-memory vector search helper will be provided if CockroachDB is offline during initial boot.

